1
00:00:01,270 --> 00:00:06,720
Episode 28
Is there a reason you wanted to see me so suddenly?

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:11,700
I thought you would have serious heartache lately, because of your son, so I contacted you immediately.

3
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:20,180
Although  I am embarrassed because my son may have tainted the orchestra's image,

4
00:00:20,180 --> 00:00:24,160
he didn't murder anyone.  He was framed.

5
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:30,700
Framed?  Are you saying he has been blamed for someone else's crime?

6
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:37,510
Is it alright if I let you in on one of my secrets?

7
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:43,600
Of course. Let it out, I like these things.

8
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:48,850
It's been said that Yun Yeong Gil, who fell in the Sinyeong building not long ago,

9
00:00:48,850 --> 00:00:54,980
was the hit-and-run driver in the accident which killed pianist Kim Ian a year ago.

10
00:00:56,180 --> 00:01:03,100
Yes, that's what the news said, but what does that have to do with your secret?

11
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:06,430
The pianist Kim Ian, who was killed in that accident,

12
00:01:06,430 --> 00:01:10,400
was actually  my son.

13
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:15,080
- Your son?
- Yes.

14
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:20,970
We were separated when he was young so I rarely saw his face.

15
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:25,820
How ... in the world ...

16
00:01:27,380 --> 00:01:31,420
That's why I said it is a secret. But you know what?

17
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:38,200
Recently I visited my oldest son,  who told me something very interesting.

18
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:40,140
What did he say?

19
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:45,000
He said Conductor Nam Ju Wan, Professor Kang Myeong Seok and the dead Yun Yeong Gil

20
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,360
are all involved in my son's case.

21
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:55,770
What is meant by that?

22
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:03,530
Well, I'm just saying that is what I heard. How will you deal with the consequences

23
00:02:03,530 --> 00:02:08,660
if the conductor and the son-in-law of Sinyeong Group are involved in a murder?

24
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:11,370
It's a bit worrisome.

25
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:25,800
- Did CEO Jang really say that?
- That's what he said.

26
00:02:26,930 --> 00:02:31,610
But, as I think about it, it's strange.

27
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:38,220
Why would the culprit of the Kim Ian hit-and-run die in our building?

28
00:02:38,220 --> 00:02:42,090
Are you positive you have nothing to do with the accident?

29
00:02:42,090 --> 00:02:47,000
Really. Why are you dragging me in? No way.

30
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:51,230
And, even if I did. Both Kim Ian and the hit-and-run driver are dead and buried.

31
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:55,000
What benefit do we gain in raking over the ashes of those incidents?

32
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:59,620
It would be nice if everything were covered up soon by public disclosure of Jang Yun's charges.

33
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:13,810
Is everything going well, Conductor?

34
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:16,970
Thanks to you.

35
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:22,700
The court released  the suspect in this case, so I kind of lost my enthusiasm for it.

36
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:25,650
So I thought a second round of interrogation was unnecessary.

37
00:03:25,650 --> 00:03:28,240
However, there's something I need to verify.

38
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,270
Please go ahead.

39
00:03:30,270 --> 00:03:36,870
According to our investigation, you and Sinyeong Music College Professor Kang Myeong Suk are very close.

40
00:03:36,870 --> 00:03:40,900
He sent you to study abroad, paid for your tuition and recommended you for the conductor post.

41
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:44,390
He has helped me a lot, since I was a student.

42
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,660
So, are you still on good terms?

43
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:48,460
What do you mean?

44
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:52,330
I mean, are you two getting along?

45
00:03:52,330 --> 00:03:54,820
Sometimes we argue.

46
00:03:55,580 --> 00:03:59,650
Did you ever argue because of the late Yun Yeong Gil?

47
00:03:59,650 --> 00:04:02,150
Yes, we did.

48
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:04,430
When?

49
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:07,440
The night of the day that Yun Yeong Gil's body was discovered.

50
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:12,570
He asked me I killed him and I said some nasty things.

51
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:15,210
I got so emotional that I spoke without thinking.

52
00:04:15,210 --> 00:04:20,090
But why did he ask you if you killed Yun Yeong Gil?

53
00:04:20,090 --> 00:04:24,420
I don't know. Call him and ask him.

54
00:04:26,890 --> 00:04:30,770
Actually, a tip-off video arrived this morning.

55
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:36,900
You've been suspecting me for a year. But do you have evidence that I killed Kim Ian?

56
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:39,030
If you do, let's see it. Say it after you show it.

57
00:04:39,030 --> 00:04:42,990
Isn't that what Yun Yeong Gil had, evidence of who killed Kim Ian?

58
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:47,590
So I killed Yun Yeong Gil in order to hide that evidence?

59
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:51,710
I can't hear it clearly, but if you watch the middle of the video,

60
00:04:51,710 --> 00:04:56,410
you said to Professor Kang that he killed Yun Yeong Gil because he had evidence that Professor Kang killed Kim Ian.

61
00:04:56,410 --> 00:04:59,340
Well, that is what you are saying.

62
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:01,480
Is that so?

63
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:05,100
- Didn't you say that?
- I don't remember.

64
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:12,390
From my perspective, you, Professor Kang, Yun Yeong Gil, and Kim Ian are all connected.

65
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:16,160
Was Yun Yeong Gil just a fan of yours?

66
00:05:16,870 --> 00:05:21,170
Yes.  He was my fan.

67
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:34,320
Do you know the stairs where Yun Yeong Gil died?

68
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:39,410
Were you ever near the exit to that stairway that day?

69
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:44,730
No, I ...  I didn't go in that direction.

70
00:06:10,130 --> 00:06:12,040
Ms. Assistant.

71
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,500
- Why are you running away?
- When did I?

72
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:22,020
- You just did as soon as you saw me.
- You know that's not so.

73
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:25,890
Are you denying you keep running away, Miss Judas?

74
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:28,100
I am not Ju Da. Get out of my way.

75
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,990
Okay. Okay.  Let's say you are not Ju Da.

76
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:36,400
- Have you eaten?
- What did you say?

77
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:41,000
- Want to have a meal together?
- I don't.

78
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,480
If not rice, what do you like to eat?

79
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:48,560
(Eating bap, "rice", in Korea is synonymous with having a meal)

80
00:06:51,890 --> 00:06:55,620
Where did you go to search for the conductor on the day of the concert?

81
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:57,390
I don't remember.

82
00:06:57,390 --> 00:07:00,620
Don't do that.  Try to remember.

83
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:06,980
You remembered precisely before that you had not gone to the exit to the stairway where Yun Yeong Gil was found.

84
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:08,810
I don't know.

85
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:16,400
Did you go to the rooftop?  If you went, I'm sure you would recall.

86
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,900
If you continue to question me that way, I'm leaving.

87
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:22,730
Excuse me.  I'm sorry.  I'm sorry.  Is there anything else you want to eat?

88
00:07:22,730 --> 00:07:26,100
Is there anything else you want to eat? Order something.

89
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:29,090
Can I have whatever I want?

90
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:31,580
Eat up.

91
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:40,570
- Do you like the conductor?
- Who said so?

92
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:43,760
Ju Da kept attacking Hong Yi Yeong.

93
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:47,830
Calling her a poodle, stuck-up, whatever.

94
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,320
So it was quite obvious.

95
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:53,550
Actually, it's correct that she is a poodle. She was picked on because she deserved it...

96
00:07:54,570 --> 00:07:59,450
You saw the conductor that day.  Where did you see him?

97
00:08:02,030 --> 00:08:07,710
If you're trying to protect the conductor because you like him, that's wrong.  That's a crime.

98
00:08:07,710 --> 00:08:10,500
Protect, who's protecting whom?  That's not so.

99
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,580
Then, what is it?

100
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:17,630
That is ... I was so frightened.

101
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:24,900
What exactly did you see that day? It's okay. Take your time and tell me.

102
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:33,610
That day. I went to look for the conductor in the hallway.

103
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:38,430
I wondered if he had gone outside because he was nervous,

104
00:08:38,430 --> 00:08:40,890
so I went outside.

105
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:55,370
I searched for him all over the rooftop,

106
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:59,400
but I didn't find him anywhere.

107
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,900
And then I happened to ...

108
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:11,600
because I thought I saw someone through a window...

109
00:09:14,060 --> 00:09:16,500
I'm leaving now.

110
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:19,590
Hey there!  Wait!

111
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:21,990
Wait!

112
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:35,310
This is driving me crazy.

113
00:10:36,420 --> 00:10:40,660
So Jang Yun really made a recording that day?

114
00:10:40,660 --> 00:10:43,330
Then did you think it was a joke?

115
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:47,650
The police have the video.  I saw it.

116
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:51,800
Damn. My face was filmed so the police will summon me.

117
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:56,300
- Are you afraid?
- Why would I be afraid? It's just a bother.

118
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:59,290
Yun Yeong Gil was your doing. Why do I have to be involved?

119
00:10:59,290 --> 00:11:01,380
You don't have any proof.

120
00:11:01,380 --> 00:11:07,400
If you continue to do that, I'll say you killed Kim Ian last year.

121
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:11,720
If not, would you like to turn yourself in with me?

122
00:11:13,430 --> 00:11:17,000
Why should I? A culprit should turn himself in.

123
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:21,430
Fine.  Let's say I'm the criminal.   There are no witnesses and Hong Yi Yeong can't remember anything.

124
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:26,200
The only people who know what happened that day are you and I, so why would I turn myself in?

125
00:11:28,380 --> 00:11:35,510
Ju Wan, you and I just have to play dumb and close our eyes.

126
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:39,880
Don't you think of your family? Don't you feel sorry for the grandmother who raised you?

127
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:43,550
What are you going to do about conducting? Can you live without music?

128
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:46,000
For you, that's your whole life, your everything.

129
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:51,800
- Are you certain Hong Yi Yeong won't ever regain her memory?
- What?

130
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:55,800
She already recalls that I was in the warehouse.

131
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:01,380
It's only a matter of time.

132
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:19,780
Wait a moment.  Wait.

133
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:23,000
What's wrong with you?  I'm going to report you.

134
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:28,590
I'm not trying to harass you.  I was waiting for you to ask a favor of you.

135
00:12:29,660 --> 00:12:32,130
The reason I'm like this ...

136
00:12:35,530 --> 00:12:38,420
is my brother died a year ago.

137
00:12:38,420 --> 00:12:41,260
Yes. It was on the news.

138
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,700
I'm looking for the man who killed my brother

139
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:48,030
and you are a witness to him committing a crime. That is what I believe.

140
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:53,610
It's not proof that he killed my brother, but it could be the key to getting him to talk.

141
00:12:53,700 --> 00:13:00,400
If you saw something that day,  I beg you to  tell me.

142
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:04,350
I promise I won't tell anyone about you.

143
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:06,900
I beg of you.

144
00:13:12,190 --> 00:13:14,500
I arrived a little early and came in.

145
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:19,600
After I get the item, I'll leave. When you come, if I'm not outside, come in.

146
00:13:21,350 --> 00:13:23,160
Oh, you're here.

147
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:26,470
Hello.  I'm sorry I left yesterday.

148
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:30,400
You're here to pick up what the late customer left.  Just a moment.

149
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:33,790
I took care to put it aside yesterday.

150
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:37,090
Here.

151
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,430
Cathedrale d'Auxerre
Bach Fugue in G Minor

152
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:44,490
Is this it? What the ahjussi left?

153
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:48,840
Yes.  It's a requiem isn't it?

154
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,130
Yes.

155
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:55,790
He used to listen to old pop music.  Why, of all things, is this a requiem?

156
00:13:55,790 --> 00:13:58,450
Is this everything?  Did he leave anything else?

157
00:13:58,450 --> 00:14:01,860
No.  That's the only thing.

158
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:09,560
Thank you. Next time, I will come  back to really listen to music.

159
00:14:11,630 --> 00:14:14,910
We see each other again, Hong Yi Yeong.

160
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:31,040
Yi Yeong!  Hey, Yi Yeong!  Hong Yi Yeong, wait!

161
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:37,400
Hey, Hong Yi Yeong! Stop.  Let's talk.

162
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:07,990
Hello.

163
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,450
Professor Kang came to the café.

164
00:15:10,450 --> 00:15:14,680
I ran away but he's following me.

165
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:17,180
I'm here near the café ...

166
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,620
Stop there. Hey!

167
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:30,400
Yi Yeong.

168
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,360
Yoon.  Behind me ...

169
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,470
Hello.

170
00:16:05,920 --> 00:16:07,880
Yi Yeong!

171
00:16:13,860 --> 00:16:16,470
1 year before

172
00:16:16,470 --> 00:16:20,290
Track 01

173
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,380
I'll let you meet him.

174
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:32,540
You want to meet him. I said I will let you meet him.

175
00:16:32,540 --> 00:16:34,250
Satisfied?

176
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:37,010
Sorry.

177
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:40,080
Please don't say that. But I have a request.

178
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:45,000
Just until we arrive at Professor Song's house, let's smile.

179
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:49,130
I don't want to be in a gloomy mood with you.

180
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,720
Yeah.

181
00:17:06,470 --> 00:17:08,210
That car's a little weird.

182
00:17:08,210 --> 00:17:09,650
Which car?

183
00:17:09,650 --> 00:17:12,780
The black car behind us.

184
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:15,300
I think it has been following us since earlier.

185
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:18,030
Us, why us?

186
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:25,120
What's the matter with that car?

187
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:41,200
Are you okay?

188
00:17:47,250 --> 00:17:50,440
Hold onto the handlebar!

189
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:03,400
Just what is he doing?  This is not going to do.  I'm going to report him.

190
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:51,010
Calm down.  It's okay.

191
00:19:53,390 --> 00:19:55,750
It's just thunder.

192
00:19:57,600 --> 00:20:03,400
Take a big breath. Take a big breath.  Let it out.

193
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:08,500
Big breath.  Let it out.

194
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:15,500
Do you want me to make you laugh within ten seconds?

195
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,270
How?

196
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:20,580
Wait.  Wait and see.

197
00:20:23,910 --> 00:20:28,130
♪ There is a man
("One Man" by Kim Jong Gook)

198
00:20:28,130 --> 00:20:31,620
♪ He loves you so much

199
00:20:31,620 --> 00:20:35,200
♪ There is a man

200
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:39,400
♪ He couldn't say he loved you

201
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:43,920
♪ If I reach my hand out to you

202
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:46,800
♪ I could touch you

203
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:57,600
♪ I'm the one who cares for you more than myself

204
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:08,950
See.   You laughed.

205
00:21:08,950 --> 00:21:12,030
You really are an awful singer.

206
00:21:12,030 --> 00:21:15,320
You know, Hong Yi Yeong?

207
00:21:15,320 --> 00:21:17,700
Yeah?

208
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:23,360
There is one thing I didn't tell you.

209
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:26,590
I should tell you now.

210
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:28,650
To me?

211
00:21:30,060 --> 00:21:31,960
What is it?

212
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:40,090
Who is it?

213
00:21:48,510 --> 00:21:50,380
Who are you?

214
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:52,300
You, who are you?

215
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:55,210
Who is doing this to us?

216
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:02,910
Who is it? Please don't come close.

217
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:04,720
Yi Yeong!

218
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:09,600
Who are you? Who are you?

219
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:16,000
Please help us, please help us, please...

220
00:22:17,760 --> 00:22:19,900
Hong Yi Yeong!

221
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:24,390
Please spare us, please...

222
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:35,560
Don't come close! I will stab you if you come close!

223
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:40,000
Yi Yeong! Hong Yi Yeong! Don't touch that woman!

224
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,420
Get out of here.

225
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:44,460
Who are you?

226
00:22:44,460 --> 00:22:48,970
There isn't much time, they will come for you soon. Use the knife to free yourself. Quickly.

227
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:51,770
Who are you?

228
00:22:54,550 --> 00:22:56,800
Sunbae Ju Wan?

229
00:23:10,210 --> 00:23:12,940
Don't waste time. Quickly get out of here!

230
00:24:00,430 --> 00:24:02,200
Are you okay?

231
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:17,300
Danger ahead!

232
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:53,430
No. No. No!

233
00:25:18,660 --> 00:25:20,930
Stay here, please.

234
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,380
Emergency Room

235
00:26:03,790 --> 00:26:06,400
Why are you still here?

236
00:26:08,180 --> 00:26:10,360
I asked why are you here.

237
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,420
Why are you with Yi Yeong?

238
00:26:12,420 --> 00:26:14,170
Go! Go!

239
00:26:14,170 --> 00:26:17,150
Stay away from Yi Yeong! Please!

240
00:26:17,150 --> 00:26:20,260
Please go away! Please!

241
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:22,050
Mom, calm down.

242
00:26:22,050 --> 00:26:24,650
- I'm sorry. Mom.
- Please stay away from us!

243
00:26:24,650 --> 00:26:28,540
Why are you with Yi Yeong?

244
00:26:28,540 --> 00:26:31,310
Please stay away...

245
00:26:38,650 --> 00:26:42,340
I am sorry but even if you stay, you can't see her.

246
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:45,310
So please leave.

247
00:26:45,310 --> 00:26:48,510
When I see her wake up, I'll leave.

248
